  "doc_id": "31716",
  "text": "Propagation of light in a turbid media is governed by radiative transport equation (RTE) [CITATION_1] , which is an integrodifferential equation and solving it is computationally too expensive. For highly scattering media (µ a << µ s ), RTE gets reduced to the diffusion equation. To model the propagation of excitation light (wavelength λ x ) as well as fluorescence light (wavelength λ m ), in domain Ω d ⊂ R d (d= 2 or 3) with boundary ∂ Ω d ,coupled diffusion equations are used: [CITATION_2] ",
